&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Humorless&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Ludicrous&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; means causing or intended to cause laughter. (हंसी पैदा करना)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;antonyms&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of the word&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Ludicrous&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; are&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;humorless,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;mournful&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;lame&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;.&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;What a &lt;strong&gt;ludicrous &lt;/strong&gt;idea!&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;From&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;antonym&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the given word, we can say that the word &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Humorless&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; is the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;opposite&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;in&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;meaning&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;Humorless&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;not being able to appreciate or express humor. (हास्य की सराहना या व्यक्त करने में सक्षम नहीं)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;She is the only one who is a cyborg, as she makes a reference to her positronic photon brain, and typically serious and &lt;strong&gt;humorless&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 4&lt;/span&gt;. Let&amp;#39;s see the&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;meaning&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of other given options:-&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;WORDS&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;MEANING&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Profuse&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;very plentiful; abundant. (बहुत भरपूर; प्रचुर)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;The flowers were so &lt;strong&gt;profuse &lt;/strong&gt;they could be seen from space.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Whimsical&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;playfully quaint or fanciful, especially in an appealing and amusing way. (विशेष रूप से आकर्षक और मनोरंजक तरीके से, विचित्र रूप से विचित्र या काल्पनिक)&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;Despite the warning, the house is &lt;strong&gt;whimsical &lt;/strong&gt;and playful.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Jovial&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;cheerful and friendly. (हंसमुख और मिलनसार)&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;He was in &lt;strong&gt;jovial &lt;/strong&gt;mood as he cast his vote in Tuscany.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;synonyms&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the word&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Ludicrous&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; are&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;funny, hilarious,&amp;nbsp;laughable&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;Ludicrous&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;in a&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&amp;nbsp;sentence&lt;/u&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;ludicrous&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;movie is about a dog that becomes the president of a country&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is-&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;have everything properly organized&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;https://cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The meaning of the given idiom is:&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Get One&amp;rsquo;s Ducks in a Row&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Complete one&amp;#39;s preparations, become efficient and well organized&lt;/em&gt;. (किसी चीज़ के लिए एक खाका एक योजना या प्रस्तावों का समूह है जो दर्शाता है कि यह कैसे काम करने की उम्मीद है)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;I&amp;#39;m trying to get my ducks in a row before I go to Europe.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;By&amp;nbsp;the above meaning and example, we can say that&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;have everything properly organized​&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the correct answer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
Hence&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 1&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;is the appropriate answer.&amp;nbsp;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Option 4&lt;/b&gt; i.e. &lt;b&gt;felicitous, luminosity&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;felicitous&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means well-suited or apt, especially in expression or style. It denotes something that is appropriate or fitting. (उपयुक्त)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The writer&amp;#39;s felicitous choice of words captured the reader&amp;#39;s imagination.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;luminosity&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; refers to the quality of being bright or radiant, often used in the context of light or brilliance. (चमक)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The luminosity of the full moon illuminated the entire landscape.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The artist&amp;rsquo;s skilled use of chiaroscuro (the contrast between light and dark) to create a sense of brilliance and subtle emotional expression aligns with the meaning of &amp;quot;felicitous&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;luminosity&amp;quot;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;The artist&amp;rsquo;s &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;felicitous&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;use of chiaroscuro created a sense of &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;luminosity&lt;/span&gt;, drawing the viewer&amp;rsquo;s eye toward the subtle emotional nuances of the subject.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Option 4&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Perfunctory, apathy&lt;/strong&gt; (सतही, उदासीनता):

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Perfunctory:&lt;/strong&gt; Done without much effort or interest. (सतही)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Apathy:&lt;/strong&gt; Lack of interest, enthusiasm, or concern. (उदासीनता)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The teacher&amp;rsquo;s perfunctory explanation reflected his apathy toward the students&amp;rsquo; understanding of the topic.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Masterly, depth&lt;/strong&gt; (निपुण, गहराई):
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Masterly:&lt;/strong&gt; Showing great skill or proficiency. (निपुण)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Depth:&lt;/strong&gt; Complexity or profundity of thought. (गहराई)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The masterly execution of the painting revealed a profound depth of emotion.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tenuous, confusion&lt;/strong&gt; (नाजुक, भ्रम):
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tenuous:&lt;/strong&gt; Weak or slight; not substantial. (नाजुक)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Confusion:&lt;/strong&gt; A state of being unclear or uncertain. (भ्रम)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The tenuous argument only added to the confusion of the situation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Option 4&lt;/b&gt; i.e. &amp;quot;aberrant, manifestation&amp;quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;aberrant&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means deviating from the usual or normal path, behavior, or standard; something that is unusual or irregular. (विकृत या असामान्य)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; His aberrant actions during the meeting surprised everyone as he was usually calm and composed.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Manifestation&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; refers to the act of showing or revealing something, especially a sign or symptom of a particular condition or phenomenon. (अभिव्यक्ति या प्रकट होना)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The sudden manifestation of fear in her eyes indicated that something was wrong.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;The patient&amp;rsquo;s &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;aberrant&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;behavior was a &lt;strong&gt;m&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;anifestation&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of a deep-seated trauma that had been suppressed for decades within the subconscious.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct pair of words that meaningfully complete the sentence is &amp;quot;aberrant&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;manifestation&amp;quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Eccentric&lt;/strong&gt; (विचित्र): Refers to someone or something that behaves in a manner that is unconventional or strange.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; His eccentric habits, like wearing mismatched socks, often amused his colleagues.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Refutation&lt;/strong&gt; (खंडन): The action of proving a statement or theory to be wrong or false.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The scientist provided a detailed refutation of the false claims made by the opposition.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Typified&lt;/strong&gt; (प्रतिमान बनाना): Represents or symbolizes a typical example of something.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; His actions typified the generosity and kindness of his family.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Negation&lt;/strong&gt; (नकार): The contradiction or denial of something.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The lawyer&amp;rsquo;s argument was a complete negation of the opposing party&amp;#39;s statement.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stoic&lt;/strong&gt; (वैराग्यपूर्ण): Refers to someone who endures pain or hardship without showing feelings or complaining.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; Despite the challenges, she remained stoic and focused on her goals.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Culmination&lt;/strong&gt; (परिणति): The highest or climactic point of something, especially after a long time.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; Winning the championship was the culmination of years of hard work and practice.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Option 3&lt;/b&gt; i.e. &lt;b&gt;interlarded, inscrutable&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;interlarded&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means to mix or insert something into another thing, often to create variety or add detail. (मिश्रित करना, सम्मिलित करना)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The author interlarded his narrative with amusing anecdotes to engage the readers.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;inscrutable&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; refers to something that is impossible to understand or interpret; mysterious. (अविवेचनीय, रहस्यमय)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The ancient script was so inscrutable that even the most experienced linguists struggled to decode it.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the sentence, the novelist&amp;#39;s prose was described as being &amp;quot;interlarded&amp;quot; with archaic idioms, making it &amp;quot;inscrutable&amp;quot; to contemporary readers.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;The novelist&amp;rsquo;s prose was so &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;interlarded&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;with archaic idioms that it rendered the narrative &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;inscrutable&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;to the contemporary reader.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Option 3&lt;/strong&gt; i.e. &lt;b&gt;interlarded, inscrutable&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 1: devoid, pellucid&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;रहित, पारदर्शी&lt;/span&gt;)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Devoid:&lt;/strong&gt; Completely lacking in something. (रहित)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The speech was devoid of any passion and failed to inspire the audience.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pellucid:&lt;/strong&gt; Extremely clear or transparent. (पारदर्शी)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The pellucid lake reflected the surrounding mountains perfectly.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2: garnished, evocative&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;सजाया हुआ, स्मरणीय&lt;/span&gt;)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Garnished:&lt;/strong&gt; Decorated or embellished, often to enhance appearance. (सजाया हुआ)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The dish was garnished with fresh herbs and looked delightful.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Evocative:&lt;/strong&gt; Bringing strong images, memories, or feelings to mind. (स्मरणीय)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The evocative music transported her to a different time and place.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 4: suffused, limpid&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;व्याप्त, स्वच्छ&lt;/span&gt;)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Suffused:&lt;/strong&gt; Gradually spread through or over. (व्याप्त)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The room was suffused with the warm glow of sunlight.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Limpid:&lt;/strong&gt; Clear and transparent, often used for liquids or writing style. (स्वच्छ)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; Her limpid prose made even complex topics accessible to readers.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Option 2 (efficacy, superlative)&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;efficacy&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means the ability to produce a desired or intended result. (प्रभावशीलता)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The efficacy of the new drug was proven through extensive clinical trials.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Superlative&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; refers to something that is of the highest quality or degree. (उत्तम)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The chef&amp;rsquo;s superlative cooking skills earned the restaurant a five-star rating.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, the pair of words &amp;quot;efficacy&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;superlative&amp;quot; correctly complete the sentence by emphasizing the catalyst&amp;#39;s ability to enhance the reaction with exceptional efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;The &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;efficacy&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of the catalyst ensured that the reaction proceeded with &lt;strong&gt;s&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;uperlative&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;efficiency, requiring significantly less activation energy than previously theorized.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Option 2 (efficacy, superlative)&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 1 (inhibition, lackluster)&lt;/strong&gt;:

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Inhibition&lt;/strong&gt; (रोक): A feeling that makes one self-conscious and unable to act naturally.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; His inhibition prevented him from speaking confidently in public.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lackluster&lt;/strong&gt; (निस्तेज): Lacking in vitality, force, or conviction; uninspired or dull.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The team&amp;#39;s lackluster performance disappointed the coach.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 3 (instability, erratic)&lt;/strong&gt;:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Instability&lt;/strong&gt; (अस्थिरता): Lack of stability; the state of being unstable.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The instability of the economy caused widespread concern.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Erratic&lt;/strong&gt; (अनियमित): Not even or regular in pattern or movement; unpredictable.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; His erratic driving behavior led to a traffic violation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 4 (viscosity, marginal)&lt;/strong&gt;:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Viscosity&lt;/strong&gt; (चिपचिपापन): The state of being thick, sticky, and semi-fluid in consistency.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The viscosity of the liquid increased as it cooled down.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Marginal&lt;/strong&gt; (सीमांत): Of secondary or minor importance; not central.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The changes made to the plan had only a marginal impact on its success.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Option 3&lt;/b&gt; i.e. &lt;b&gt;reconditeness, impenetrable&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;reconditeness&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means the quality of being difficult to understand or obscure. (गूढ़ता)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;The professor&amp;rsquo;s lecture was filled with reconditeness, making it hard for students to follow.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;impenetrable&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; refers to something that cannot be understood or penetrated easily. (अभेद्य)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;The dense fog made the path ahead appear impenetrable.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the context of the sentence, the philosopher&amp;#39;s argument was so profound and difficult to comprehend that even experts found it impossible to discern the underlying framework. This matches the combination of &amp;quot;reconditeness&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;impenetrable&amp;quot;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;The philosopher&amp;rsquo;s argument was characterized by such profound &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;reconditeness&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;that even seasoned scholars found it &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;impenetrable&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;to discern the underlying teleological framework.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Option 3&lt;/strong&gt; i.e., &lt;strong&gt;reconditeness, impenetrable&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 1: perspicacity, arduous&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Perspicacity&lt;/strong&gt; (तीक्ष्णबुद्धि): The quality of having a ready insight into things; shrewdness.

		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; Her perspicacity in identifying complex problems is remarkable.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Arduous&lt;/strong&gt; (कठिन): Involving or requiring strenuous effort; difficult and tiring.
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; Climbing the steep mountain was an arduous task.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;

	&lt;p&gt;This option does not fit the context, as the sentence requires words that emphasize obscurity, not insight or difficulty.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2: opacity, grueling&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Opacity&lt;/strong&gt; (अस्पष्टता): The quality of being difficult to understand or unclear.
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The opacity of his arguments left the audience confused.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Grueling&lt;/strong&gt; (थकाऊ): Extremely tiring and demanding.
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The marathon was grueling for the participants.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;

	&lt;p&gt;While &amp;quot;opacity&amp;quot; fits the context, &amp;quot;grueling&amp;quot; does not match the sentence, as it focuses on effort rather than understanding.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 4: lucidity, taxing&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lucidity&lt;/strong&gt; (स्पष्टता): Clarity of expression; intelligibility.
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The lucidity of her writing made the complex topic easy to understand.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Taxing&lt;/strong&gt; (थकाऊ): Physically or mentally demanding.
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The taxing schedule left little time for leisure.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;

	&lt;p&gt;This option does not fit the sentence, as &amp;quot;lucidity&amp;quot; contradicts the idea of something being difficult to understand.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Option 1&lt;/b&gt; i.e., &amp;quot;ameliorate, recalcitrant&amp;quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;ameliorate&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means to make something better or improve a situation. (सुधारना)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The new policies were introduced to ameliorate the living conditions of workers.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;recalcitrant&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; refers to someone or something that is stubbornly resistant to authority or control. (अवज्ञाकारी)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The manager had a hard time dealing with recalcitrant employees who refused to follow instructions.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The sentence discusses the central bank&amp;#39;s attempts to improve (ameliorate) the economic situation, but the market remains stubborn and uncooperative (recalcitrant). Hence, these words fit the blanks perfectly.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Despite the central bank&amp;rsquo;s attempts to &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;ameliorate&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;the looming recession through aggressive quantitative easing, the market remained &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;recalcitrant&lt;/span&gt;, refusing to respond to the influx of liquidity.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Option 1&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2: exacerbate, buoyant&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Exacerbate&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; (बढ़ाना/बिगाड़ना): To make a problem, situation, or negative feeling worse.

		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; His rude comments only served to exacerbate the tension in the room.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Buoyant&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; (प्रसन्नचित्त/उत्साही): Cheerful and optimistic, or able to float in water.
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The stock market remained buoyant despite the global economic slowdown.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;

	&lt;p&gt;This option is incorrect because &amp;quot;exacerbate&amp;quot; means to worsen, which does not fit the context of trying to improve the economic situation.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 3: palliate, malleable&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Palliate&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; (कम करना): To reduce the severity of something, especially pain or a problem.
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The doctor gave her medicine to palliate the symptoms of her illness.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Malleable&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; (लचीला): Capable of being easily shaped or influenced.
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; Gold is a highly malleable metal.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;

	&lt;p&gt;This option is incorrect because &amp;quot;malleable&amp;quot; suggests flexibility or adaptability, which does not fit the description of the market in the sentence.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 4: obviate, volatile&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Obviate&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; (निवारण करना): To remove a need or difficulty; to prevent something.
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; Regular exercise can obviate the need for medication in some cases.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Volatile&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; (अस्थिर): Likely to change suddenly and unpredictably, especially for the worse.
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The political situation in the region remains highly volatile.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;

	&lt;p&gt;This option is incorrect because &amp;quot;obviate&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;volatile&amp;quot; do not appropriately describe the context of the sentence.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Option 2 i.e. lacunary, conjectural.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;lacunary&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; refers to something that is incomplete, having gaps or missing parts. (अपूर्ण, रिक्त स्थान वाला)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The lacunary manuscript made it difficult for historians to piece together the complete story.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Conjectural&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means based on conjecture or speculation rather than facts or certainty. (कल्पनात्मक)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The scientist&amp;#39;s theory was purely conjectural, as no concrete evidence supported it.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, the sentence conveys that the incomplete nature of the fossil record often leads to speculative conclusions, which matches perfectly with the pair of words &amp;quot;lacunary&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;conjectural&amp;quot;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;The &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;lacunary&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;nature of the fossil record often leads to &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;conjectural&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;conclusions, as paleontologists are forced to extrapolate complex physiological traits from mere skeletal fragments.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Option 2 i.e. lacunary, conjectural.&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Exhaustive&lt;/strong&gt; (विस्तृत): Thorough and comprehensive in covering all aspects.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The professor gave an exhaustive explanation of the topic, leaving no questions unanswered.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Definitive&lt;/strong&gt; (निर्णायक): Conclusive and authoritative.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The Supreme Court&amp;#39;s ruling was definitive, leaving no room for appeal.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pristine&lt;/strong&gt; (अदूषित): In its original condition; unspoiled.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The pristine beaches of the island attract tourists from all over the world.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Speculative&lt;/strong&gt; (कल्पनात्मक): Based on conjecture rather than knowledge.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The speculative nature of the report made its findings questionable.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
